ygData.messageBody:
As far as being underpowered....i doubt they stay that way. Its a high
difficulty class as other have said. Its a hybrd class...as others have
said. But I think, in my honest opinion that it will become one of the
most powerfull eventually. But that power comes with a price...it takes
time and patience...and I think that the only things the SK requires to
become great is that time and patience, everything else will fall in line.
Later. Have faith brothers.....and if I'm worng...so be it...still a very
fun and challanging class to play and be.

Korm
